                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <head>No. 411.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Morgan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 22, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 421.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    638, of the 4th instant, concerning the case of Captain Caleb, of the Adriana,
                    and to say that the Department duly appreciates the courtesy of Señor Romero
                    Rubio, whom you consulted with reference to certain proceedings respecting the
                    same.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
